SP  - 161
EP  - 196
VL  - 58
IS  - 1
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1540-6261.00521
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper presents a new test of conditional versions of the Sharpe-Lintner CAPM, the Jagannathan and Wang (1996) extension of the CAPM, and the Fama and French (1993) three-factor model. The test is based on a general nonparametric methodology that avoids functional form misspecification of betas, risk premia, and the stochastic discount factor. Our results provide a novel view of empirical performance of these models. In particular, we find that a nonparametric version of the Fama and French model performs well, even when challenged by momentum portfolios.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - New Evidence on the Market for Directors: Board Membership and Pennsylvania Senate Bill 1310
AU  - Coles, Jeffrey L.
AU  - Hoi, Chun-Keung
Y1  - 2003/02/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/02/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1540-6261.00522
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 197
EP  - 230
VL  - 58
IS  - 1
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1540-6261.00522
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We examine the relation between a board' decision to reject antitakeover provisions of Pennsylvania Senate Bill 1310 and subsequent labor market opportunities of those same board members. Compared to directors retaining all provisions, directors rejecting all protective provisions of SB1310 are three times as likely to gain additional external directorships and are 30 percent more likely to retain their internal slot on the board of that same Pennsylvania company. For external board seats, the results are driven by nonexecutive directors who are not members of the management team; for internal board seats, the results are driven by executive directors.
ER  - 

